div.p:
Inquisitio in summam seriei \frac{1}{1}+\frac{1}{4}+\frac{1}{9}+\frac{1}{16}+\frac{1}{25}\mboxy{\&c}

Sit summa quæaesita s. Ponatur Q=\frac{1}{1}+\frac{1}{9}+\mbox{ \&c} erit s=Q-\frac{1}{4}S sive \frac{3}{4}S=Q vel S=\frac{4}{3}Q. sed

Q = quadto seriei 1-\frac{1}{3}+\frac{1}{5}-\mbox{ \&c.} dempta dupla summa rectangulorum singulorum binorum terminorum

ejusdem seriei. Ponantur a=\frac{1}{1\cdot3}+\frac{1}{3\cdot5}+\frac{1}{5\cdot7}+\frac{1}{7\cdot9}+\mbox{\&c}
b=\frac{1}{1\cdot5}+\frac{1}{3\cdot7}+\frac{1}{5\cdot9}+\mbox{\&c}
c=\frac{1}{1\cdot7}+\frac{1}{3\cdot9}+\mbox{\&c}

d=\frac{1}{1\cdot9}+\frac{1}{3\cdot11}+\mbox{\&c}
e=\frac{1}{1\cdot11}+\frac{1}{3\cdot13}+\mbox{\&c} et ita porrò. Ponantur item q=\frac{1}{1}-\frac{1}{3}+\frac{1}{5}-\frac{1}{7}\mbox{ \&c} eritque Q=qq+2a

-2b+2c-2d+2e\mbox{ \&c.} Est autem a=\frac{1}{2}\times\frac{1}{1},b=\frac{1}{4}\times(\frac{1}{1}+\frac{1}{3}),c=\frac{1}{6}\times(\frac{1}{1}+\frac{1}{3}+\frac{1}{5}).d=\frac{1}{8}\times(\frac{1}{1}+\frac{1}{3}+\frac{1}{5}+\frac{1}{7})e=\frac{1}{10}

\times(\frac{1}{1}+\frac{1}{3}+\frac{1}{5}+\frac{1}{7}+\frac{1}{9})\mbox{ \&c.} Oriuntur enim series a,b,c,d,e,\mbox{ \&c} substrahendo seriem \frac{1}{1}+\frac{1}{3}+\frac{1}{5}+\frac{1}{7}\mbox{ \&c.}

mutilatam uno, duobus, tribus &etc. primis terminis à se ipsa integra et dividendo reliquum respe-
ctive per 2, 4, 6 &c. quibus valoribus substitutis invenietur Q=qq+\frac{1}{1}-\frac{1}{2}\times\left(\frac{1}{1}+\frac{1}{3}\right)+\frac{1}{3}\times\left(\frac{1}{1}+\frac{1}{3}+\frac{1}{5}\right) 
-\frac{1}{4}\times\left(\frac{1}{1}+\frac{1}{3}+\frac{1}{5}+\frac{1}{7}\right)+\frac{1}{5}\times\left(\frac{1}{1}+\frac{1}{3}+\frac{1}{5}+\frac{1}{7}+\frac{1}{9}\right)-\mbox{\&c}=qq+\frac{1}{1}-\frac{4}{2\cdot1\cdot3}+\frac{23}{3\cdot1\cdot3\cdot5}-\frac{176}{4\cdot1\cdot3\cdot5\cdot7}+\frac{1689}{5\cdot1\cdot3\cdot5\cdot7\cdot9}-\frac{19524}{6\cdot1\cdot3\cdot5\cdot7\cdot9\cdot11}

+\mbox{\&c}. Summa hujus seriei (quæae vocetur y) ita ut sit Q=qq+y) Nb. expeditius investigatur {*} 

Nb. Il y avoit  une autre methode pour trouver la valeur de y

Multo expeditius hoc modo: -\frac{1}{2}\times\left(1+\frac{1}{3}\right)=-\frac{2}{1\cdot3};+\frac{1}{3}\times\left(1+\frac{1}{3}+\frac{1}{5}\right)=\frac{2}{1\cdot5}+\frac{1}{3\cdot3};-\frac{1}{4}\times\left(1+\frac{1}{3}+\frac{1}{5}+\frac{1}{7}\right)=-\frac{2}{1\cdot7}-\frac{2}{3\cdot5}

+\frac{1}{5}\times\left(1+\frac{1}{3}+\frac{1}{5}+\frac{1}{7}+\frac{1}{9}\right)=\frac{2}{1\cdot9}+\frac{2}{3\cdot7}+\frac{1}{5\cdot5};-\frac{1}{6}\times\left(1+\frac{1}{3}+\frac{1}{5}+\frac{1}{7}+\frac{1}{9}+\frac{1}{11}\right)=-\frac{2}{1\cdot11}-\frac{2}{3\cdot9}-\frac{2}{5\cdot7}

+\frac{1}{7}\times\left(1+\frac{1}{3}+\frac{1}{5}+\frac{1}{7}\frac{1}{9}+\frac{1}{11}+\frac{1}{13}\right)=\frac{2}{1\dot{1}3}+\frac{2}{3\cdot11}+\frac{2}{5\cdot9}+\frac{1}{7\cdot7}; et hinc y=1+\frac{1}{3\cdot3}+\frac{1}{5\cdot5}+\frac{1}{7\cdot7}+\frac{1}{9\cdot9}+\frac{1}{11\cdot11}+\mbox{\&c}-\frac{2}{1\cdot3}+\frac{2}{1\cdot5}-\frac{2}{1\cdot7}+\frac{2}{1\cdot9}-\frac{2}{1\cdot11}+\frac{2}{1\cdot13}-\mbox{\&c}-\frac{2}{3\cdot5}+\frac{2}{3\cdot7}-\frac{2}{3\cdot9}+\frac{2}{3\cdot11}-\mbox{\&c}-\frac{2}{5\cdot7}+\frac{2}{5\cdot9}-\mbox{\&c}.=\left(1-\frac{1}{3}+\frac{1}{5}-\frac{1}{7}+\frac{1}{9}\right)^{2}=qq=\frac{1}{16^{pp}}.

mutando eam in aliam cujus omnes termini sint affirmativi, quod fieri potest conjungendo

dimidia duorum quorumlibet terminorum contiguorum. Nimirum y=\frac{1}{2\cdot1}+\frac{1}{2\cdot1\cdot3}-\frac{7}{2\cdot3\cdot1\cdot3\cdot5}

+\frac{58}{3\cdot4\cdot1\cdot3\cdot5\cdot7}-\frac{582}{4\cdot5\cdot1\cdot3\cdot5\cdot7\cdot9}+\frac{6927}{5\cdot6\cdot1\cdots11}-\mbox{\&c.}=\frac{1}{2\cdot1}+\frac{1}{4\cdot1\cdot3}+\frac{2}{3\cdot1\cdot3\cdot5}\frac{20}{3\cdot4\cdot1\cdot3\cdot5\dot{7}}

+\frac{144}{4\cdot5\cdot1\cdot3\cdot5\cdot7\cdot9}-\frac{1338}{5\cdot6\cdot1\cdots11}+\mbox{\&c}\frac{1}{2\cdot1}+\frac{1}{4\dot{1}\cdot3}+\frac{2}{6\cdot1\cdot3\dot{5}}+\frac{6}{4\cdot1\cdots7}-\frac{78}{4\cdot5\cdot1\cdots9}

+\frac{519}{5\cdot6\cdot1\cdots11}-\mbox{\&c}=\frac{1}{2\cdot1}+\frac{1}{4\cdot1\cdot3}+\frac{2}{6\cdot1\cdot3\cdot5}+\frac{6}{8\cdot1\cdots7}+\frac{24}{5\cdot1\cdots9}-\frac{384}{5\cdot6\cdot1\cdots11}

+\mbox{\&c}=\frac{1}{2\cdot1}+\frac{1}{4\cdot1\cdot3}+\frac{2}{6\cdot1\cdot3\cdot5}+\frac{6}{8\cdot1\cdots7}+\frac{24}{10\cdot1\cdots9}+\frac{120}{6\cdot1\cdots11}\mbox{\&c} ita ut tandem in

terminis mere affirmativis habeatur y=\frac{1}{2\cdot1}+\frac{1}{4\cdot1\cdot3}+\frac{1\cdot2}{6\cdot1\cdot3\cdot5}+\frac{1\cdot2\cdot3}{8\cdot1\cdots7}+\frac{1\cdot2\cdot3\cdot4}{10\cdot1\cdots9}+ 
\frac{1\cdot2\cdot3\cdot4\cdot5}{1\cdot2\cdot1\cdots11}+\mbox{\&c}. cujus seriei progressio manifesta est. Si enim T significet terminum

quemvis ordine n, & T' termi num sequentem, cujus ordo sit n+1, erit generaliter

nnT=(n+1)(2n+1)Tl. Cum vero relatio horum terminorum componatur ex quantitatibus

in quibus indeterminata n ascendit ad duas dimensiones, hoc indicio est summam dictæae seriei

definiri per æaequationem differentialem secundi gradus. Proponatur enim invenienda summa

sequentis seriei generalis y=Ax+Bx^{2}+Cx^{3}+Dx^{4}....+Tx^{n}+T^{l}x^{n-1}+\mbox{ } in qua sit

generaliter (a.n(n-1)+bn+c)T=e.n(n-1)+f(n+1)+g) T' id est (b+c)A=

(2e+2f+g)B et (2a+3b+c)B=(be+3f+g)C,et (6a+3b+c)C=(12e+4f+g)D,

et (12a+4b+c)D=(20e+5f+g)E\mbox{ \&c.} Summa ejus definietur per sequentem æaequa-
tionem sumpta Dx constante, gy\,dx^{2}+fx\,dy\,dx+ex^{2}\,ddy=gAx\,dx^{2}+fAx\,dx^{2}+cαxy\,dx^{2}

+bx^{2}\,dy\,dx+ax^{3}\,ddy. Nam hæaec æaequatio, positis y=Ax+Bx^{2}+Cx^{3}+Dx^{4}+Ex^{5}+\mbox{ \&c. }

dy=dx(A+2Bx+3Cx^{2}+4Dx^{3}+3Ex^{4}\mbox{ \&c })\,ddy=dx^{2}(2B+60x+12Dx^{2}+20Ex^{3}+\mbox{ \&c }) et diviso

utrimque per dx^{2}, transit in hanc

gAx+gBx^{2}+gCx^{3}+gDx^{4}+gEx^{5}\mbox{ \&c }=gAx+gBx^{2}+gCx^{3}+gDx^{4}+gEx^{5}\mbox{ \&c }

+fAx+2fBx^{2}+3fCx^{3}+4fDx^{4}+5fEx^{5}+fAx+2fBx^{2}+3fCx^{3}+4fDx^{4}+3fEx^{5}\mbox{ \&c }

+2eBx^{2}+6eCx^{3}+12eDx^{4}+20eEx^{5}+2eBx^{2}+6eCx^{3}+12eDx^{4}+20eEx^{5}\mbox{ \&c}

ubi omnes termini homogenei se invicem destruunt. Quod si igitur proponatur



summanda series y=\frac{1}{2\cdot1}x+\frac{1}{4\cdot1\cdot3}x^{2}+\frac{1\cdot2}{6\cdot1\cdot3\cdot5}x^{3}+\frac{1\cdot2\cdot3}{8\cdot1\cdot3\cdot5\cdot7}x^{4}+\mbox{\&c} in qua est A=\frac{1}{2}

et nnT=(n+1)(2n+1)T', sive (n(n-1)+n)T=(2(n+1)n+n+1)Tl et per consequens 

a=1,b=1,c=0,e=2,f=1,g=0, his valoribus in superiori æaequatione differentiali

substitutis obtinebitur x\,dy\,dx+2xx\,ddy=\frac{1}{2}x\,dx^{2}+xx\,dy\,dx+x^{3}\,ddy, sive (per x dividendo

et per dy multiplicando) dy^{2}\,dx+2x\,dy\,ddy=\frac{1}{2}\,dy\,dx^{2}+x\,dy^{2}\,dx+xx\,dy\,ddy, cujus integralis

est x\,dy^{2}=\frac{1}{2}y\,dx^{2}+\frac{1}{2}x^{2}\,dy^{2}, quæae æaequatio separatis indeterminatis, evadit \frac{dy^{2}}{y}=\frac{dx}{2x-xx}

sive \frac{dy}{sqrt{y}}=\frac{dx}{\sqrt{(2x-xx)}} cujus integralis est 2\sqrt{y}=\int\frac{dx}{\sqrt{2x-xx}}. Quia vero \int\frac{dx}{\sqrt{2x-xx}} dependet

à longitudine arcus circularis et in casu ubi x=s, æaequa lis quadranti circuli cujus

radius =1, vel semicircunferentiæae circuli cujus diameter =1, et quia q=\frac{1}{1}-\frac{1}{3}+\frac{1}{5}-\frac{1}{7}+\mbox{ \&c}

denotat etiam longitudinem quadrantis circuli cujus diameter =1,si peripheria

ejus integra vocetur p, erit q=\frac{1}{4}p, et 2\sqrt{y}=\frac{1}{2}p, sive y=\frac{1}{16}pp. Hinc Q=qq

+y=\frac{1}{8}pp & S=\frac{4}{3}Q=\frac{1}{6}pp. Q. E. D.
